<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="487" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,1190,1503]" pageId="28" pageNumber="487">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1334,1359]" pageId="28" pageNumber="487">Remarks.</emphasis>
Fowler’s (1936) reference to 
<collectingRegion box="[653,746,1334,1359]" country="Portugal" name="Madeira" pageId="28" pageNumber="487">Madeira</collectingRegion>
is based on 
<bibRefCitation box="[888,1092,1335,1359]" pageId="28" pageNumber="487" refId="ref23875" refString="Lowe, R. T. (1838) A synopsis of the fishes of Madeira; with the principal synonyms, Portuguese names, and characteres of the new Genera and Species. Transactions of the Zoological Society of London, 2, Part 3 (14), 173 - 200." type="journal article">Lowe (1838: 194)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation box="[1148,1380,1334,1359]" pageId="28" pageNumber="487" refId="ref22842" refString="Gunther, A. (1870) Catalogue of the Fishes in the British Museum. Vol. 8. British Museum (Natural History), London, 549 pp." type="book">Günther (1870: 385)</bibRefCitation>
who recorded 
<emphasis box="[261,447,1370,1395]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="487">
<taxonomicName box="[261,443,1370,1395]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Triakidae" genus="Mustelus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="487" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="laevis">Mustelus laevis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
now considered as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[865,1215,1370,1395]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Triakidae" genus="Galeorhinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="487" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mustelus">
<emphasis box="[865,1006,1370,1395]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="487">M. mustelus</emphasis>
(Linnaeus, 1758)
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[1235,1431,1371,1395]" pageId="28" pageNumber="487" refId="ref21797" refString="Compagno, L. J. V. (1973) Carcharhinidae. In: Hureau, J. - C. &amp; Monod, Th. (Eds.), Check-list of the fishes of the north-eastern Atlantic and of the Mediterranean. Unesco, Paris, pp. 23 - 31." type="book chapter">Compagno 1973</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[151,418,1406,1431]" pageId="28" pageNumber="487" refId="ref22295" refString="Eschmeyer, W. N., Fricke, R. &amp; Van der Laan, R. (Eds). Catalog of fishes: genera, species, references. Available from: http: // researcharchive. calacademy. org / research / ichthyology / catalog / fishcatmain. asp (accessed 1 June 2017)" type="book">
Eschmeyer 
<emphasis box="[286,339,1406,1431]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="487">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
). No specimens or other material from 
<collectingRegion box="[885,978,1406,1431]" country="Portugal" name="Madeira" pageId="28" pageNumber="487">Madeira</collectingRegion>
were found in natural history museum collections. According to 
<bibRefCitation box="[450,674,1442,1467]" pageId="28" pageNumber="487" refId="ref21916" refString="Compagno, L. J. V. (1984 b) FAO Species Catalogue. Vol. 4. Sharks of the world: an annotated and illustraded catalogue of shark species known to date. Part 2. Carcharhiniformes. In: FAO Fisheries Synopsis. Vol. 4. FAO, Rome, pp. 251 - 655." type="book">Compagno (1984b)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mitchill" baseAuthorityYear="1815" box="[690,790,1444,1467]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Triakidae" genus="Mustelus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="487" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="canis">
<emphasis box="[690,790,1444,1467]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="487">M. canis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the western Atlantic Ocean and Gulf of 
<collectingRegion box="[151,239,1478,1503]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="28" pageNumber="487">
<collectingCountry box="[151,239,1478,1503]" name="Mexico" pageId="28" pageNumber="487">Mexico</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
, therefore this species should be excluded from the list of Chondrichthyans of 
<collectingRegion box="[1120,1217,1478,1503]" country="Portugal" name="Madeira" pageId="28" pageNumber="487">Madeira</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
