<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="487" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,1550,1827]" pageId="28" pageNumber="487">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1658,1683]" pageId="28" pageNumber="487">Remarks.</emphasis>
The origin of this record seems to be the map given by 
<bibRefCitation box="[981,1206,1658,1683]" pageId="28" pageNumber="487" refId="ref21143" refString="Branstetter, S. (1984 b) Triakidae. In: Whitehead, P. J. P., Bauchot, M. - L., Hureau, J. - C. &amp; Tortonese, E. (Eds.), Fishes of the North-eastern Atlantic and the Mediterranean. Unesco, Paris, pp. 117 - 121." type="book chapter">Branstetter (1984b)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation box="[1220,1436,1658,1683]" pageId="28" pageNumber="487" refId="ref27192" refString="Wirtz, P., Fricke, R. &amp; Biscoito, M. J. (2008) The coastal fishes of Madeira Island - new records and an annotated check-list. Zootaxa, 1715, 1 - 26." type="journal article">
Wirtz 
<emphasis box="[1292,1344,1658,1683]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="487">et al</emphasis>
. (2008)
</bibRefCitation>
considered this a very doubtful record from 
<collectingRegion box="[653,750,1694,1719]" country="Portugal" name="Madeira" pageId="28" pageNumber="487">Madeira</collectingRegion>
. In the eastern Atlantic, this Mediterranean species seems to occur only in continental coasts, from 
<collectingCountry box="[585,686,1730,1755]" name="Gibraltar" pageId="28" pageNumber="487">Gibraltar</collectingCountry>
to the 
<collectingCountry box="[766,940,1730,1755]" name="Western Sahara" pageId="28" pageNumber="487">Western Sahara</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[956,1163,1730,1755]" pageId="28" pageNumber="487" refId="ref21916" refString="Compagno, L. J. V. (1984 b) FAO Species Catalogue. Vol. 4. Sharks of the world: an annotated and illustraded catalogue of shark species known to date. Part 2. Carcharhiniformes. In: FAO Fisheries Synopsis. Vol. 4. FAO, Rome, pp. 251 - 655." type="book">Compagno 1984b</bibRefCitation>
). Since no specimens or other material from 
<collectingRegion box="[376,469,1766,1791]" country="Portugal" name="Madeira" pageId="28" pageNumber="487">Madeira</collectingRegion>
were found in natural history museum collections, at this point, this species should be excluded from the list of chondrichthyans of 
<collectingRegion box="[655,752,1802,1827]" country="Portugal" name="Madeira" pageId="28" pageNumber="487">Madeira</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
